      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NASANA NZ (4) is a newcomer to the Jackson Painting yard from NZ. Beaten less than 6m at her latest appearance at Addington in March. She looks nicely placed to kick off in Australia with a win. CAPTAIN JAZZ (3) drew on the back row and broke last start but still managed to finish 1.2 metres from the winner in second at Parkes when second-up last Sunday. Likely to get the favours from this nice draw and both career wins have come at this distance. She may be ready to peak third up. ANYONEFORADRINK (2) gets her lowest draw of the campaign so far. Freshened since tackling a Nutrien heat but this is easier and she won her lone third-up attempt so could peak here. KALYPSO RAINBOW (9) has put together a series of decent efforts when fifth or better. Draws for a trail and so has to come into calculations for exotics.",
